<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.4.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2026-03-06T14:23:18+00:00</updated><id>https://somnathtagore.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">I build World Models. Tumors break them.</title><subtitle>We build generalizable, uncertainty-aware world models for tumor evolution and metastasis, models that (i) learn causal/functional links from genotype to regulatory state to phenotype, (ii) explicitly represent measurement noise and batch effects in real sequencing data, and (iii) transfer across cancers, tissues, and platforms. The scientific payoff is how somatic/germline variation rewires regulatory programs, how early genetic events bias invasive and metastatic routes, and how chromosomal instability (CIN) and tumor-intrinsic programs enable organ-specific colonization. The translational payoff is cheaper, scalable profiling and cleaner data, enabling robust biomarkers and therapeutic hypotheses.
</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Welcome to my research blog</title><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2026/welcome-to-my-blog/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Welcome to my research blog" /><published>2026-03-06T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-06T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2026/welcome-to-my-blog</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2026/welcome-to-my-blog/"><![CDATA[<p>Welcome to my research blog.</p>

<p>I use this space to share brief updates on my work in cancer genomics, single-cell and spatial biology, and AI-based world models for tumor evolution and metastasis.</p>

<p>My research focuses on how genomic alterations reshape regulatory programs, how early events bias metastatic trajectories, and how uncertainty-aware computational models can improve biological discovery and translation.</p>

<p>Here I will post:</p>
<ul>
  <li>research updates,</li>
  <li>method development notes,</li>
  <li>publication highlights,</li>
  <li>grant and project ideas,</li>
  <li>and perspectives on computational oncology.</li>
</ul>

<p>Thank you for visiting.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="blog" /><category term="cancer genomics" /><category term="single-cell" /><category term="spatial transcriptomics" /><category term="AI" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Research notes on cancer genomics, single-cell biology, and AI-driven modeling.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with giscus comments</title><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/giscus-comments/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with giscus comments" /><published>2022-12-10T15:59:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-12-10T15:59:00+00:00</updated><id>https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/giscus-comments</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/giscus-comments/"><![CDATA[<p>This post shows how to add GISCUS comments.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="sample-posts" /><category term="external-services" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[an example of a blog post with giscus comments]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Displaying External Posts on Your al-folio Blog</title><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/displaying-external-posts-on-your-al-folio-blog/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Displaying External Posts on Your al-folio Blog" /><published>2022-04-23T23:20:09+00:00</published><updated>2022-04-23T23:20:09+00:00</updated><id>https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/displaying-external-posts-on-your-al-folio-blog</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/displaying-external-posts-on-your-al-folio-blog/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with redirect</title><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/redirect/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with redirect" /><published>2022-02-01T17:39:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-02-01T17:39:00+00:00</updated><id>https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/redirect</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2022/redirect/"><![CDATA[<p>Redirecting to another page.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[you can also redirect to assets like pdf]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with diagrams</title><link href="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2021/diagrams/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with diagrams" /><published>2021-07-04T17:39:00+00:00</published><updated>2021-07-04T17:39:00+00:00</updated><id>https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2021/diagrams</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://somnathtagore.github.io/blog/2021/diagrams/"><![CDATA[<p>This theme supports generating various diagrams from a text description using <a href="https://github.com/zhustec/jekyll-diagrams" target="\_blank">jekyll-diagrams</a> plugin.
Below, we generate a few examples of such diagrams using languages such as <a href="https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid/" target="\_blank">mermaid</a>, <a href="https://plantuml.com/" target="\_blank">plantuml</a>, <a href="https://vega.github.io/vega-lite/" target="\_blank">vega-lite</a>, etc.</p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> different diagram-generation packages require external dependencies to be installed on your machine.
Also, be mindful of that because of diagram generation the fist time you build your Jekyll website after adding new diagrams will be SLOW.
For any other details, please refer to <a href="https://github.com/zhustec/jekyll-diagrams" target="\_blank">jekyll-diagrams</a> README.</p>

<h2 id="mermaid">Mermaid</h2>

<p>Install mermaid using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">node.js</code> package manager <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">npm</code> by running the following command:</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>npm <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="nt">-g</span> mermaid.cli
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The diagram below was generated by the following code:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>{% mermaid %}
sequenceDiagram
    participant John
    participant Alice
    Alice-&gt;&gt;John: Hello John, how are you?
    John--&gt;&gt;Alice: Great!
{% endmermaid %}
</code></pre></div></div>

